Sensitivity Analysis parameters

Source: R/data.R
l_sensitivity_parameters.Rd

This list contains the raw parameters used for the probabilistic sensitivity analysis (PSA) and deterministic sensitivity analysis (DSA). Each parameter includes its mean, standard error (se), lower and upper bounds of the 95% confidence interval, and the distribution type.

Usage

l_sensitivity_parameters

Format

A list with the following components:

body_weight

A list with the following elements:

mean

Mean body weight.

se

Standard error of the mean.

lower_ci

Lower bound of the 95% confidence interval.

upper_ci

Upper bound of the 95% confidence interval.

distribution

Distribution type, here "normal".

GD2_unit_price

A list with the following elements:

mean

Mean unit price for GD2.

se

Standard error of the mean.

lower_ci

Lower bound of the 95% confidence interval.

upper_ci

Upper bound of the 95% confidence interval.

distribution

Distribution type, here "gamma".

TT_unit_price

A list with the following elements:

mean

Mean unit price for TT.

se

Standard error of the mean.

lower_ci

Lower bound of the 95% confidence interval.

upper_ci

Upper bound of the 95% confidence interval.

distribution

Distribution type, here "gamma".

A list with the following elements:

lower_ci

upper_ci

distribution
